# {{NAME}} - WebDAV connection skill (project-with-reflect)

Facts live in this folder's `{{NAME}}.md` frontmatter and `connection.json` (transport: webdav).
The remote is operated through `rclone`; secrets live in rclone's config or an external secret store,
never printed, logged, or written to the vault.

## Before acting
1. Load `{{NAME}}.md` - remote name, vault/path conventions, setup notes, usage, and learned quirks
   (`## Quirks`). Apply them instead of rediscovering them.
2. Load `connection.json` for the hard facts (`rclone_remote`, `vault_root`, `base_url`, docs).
3. Ground in `docs_url` for non-trivial or unfamiliar WebDAV/rclone behavior.
4. Read-only commands run freely. Confirm before destructive sync/delete/move operations.
5. Auto-log notable events to `log.md`: a working recipe, an error + fix, a rate/sync gotcha.

## Actions
- `ls <path>` - list with `rclone lsf` / `rclone lsd` against the configured remote or vault root.
- `push <local> <remote-path>` - upload/overwrite one file with `rclone copyto`.
- `pull <remote-path> <local>` - download one file with `rclone copyto`.
- `sync <local-dir> <remote-dir>` - `rclone sync` a directory. Confirm first; sync deletes extras
  on the destination.
- `<rclone-subcmd ...>` - run the requested rclone command against the configured remote.
- `checkin` - **pick up + get ready**: verify the remote is reachable (`rclone lsd <remote>:` or the
  path from `connection.json`), apply learned quirks, and **must re-run title sync every time**:
  Terminal/iTerm2 via `term-title.sh "{{NAME}}"` (no-ops off a real terminal; never surface its output),
  plus Codex/Claude app thread/session title via native title tools when available (resolve the active
  thread/session first if needed; skip only when no reliable tool/lookup exists), then auto-run `status`.
- `status` - a **smart brief**: the facts (remote / root / docs) + reachable? + quirk count + the
  most recent `log.md` line. Read-only.
- `update "<content>"` - fold reference material into this note's body sections (`## Setup`,
  `## Usage`, `## Gotchas`): merge + dedupe, lean. Secrets stay outside the vault.
- `note "..."` - force a line into `log.md`.
- `reflect` - fold `log.md` into the `## Quirks` section of `{{NAME}}.md`, then archive
  (`reflect.sh archive-entity {{DIR}}`).
- `help` - this menu.

Setup, usage, rate limits, sync latency, conflict behavior, and gotchas live in `{{NAME}}.md`;
reflect maintains them. Lean.
